The paper proposes a new exploration strategy for reinforcement learning, which involves using variational inference in Bayesian neural networks to handle continuous state and action spaces. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
